replacement. Lay is no stranger to the job, having served as CEO from 1985 u=
ntil Skilling became CEO in January. During Lay's 15 years at the helm, he t=
ransformed Enron from a regional natural-gas pipeline company into the world=
's largest energy-trading company -- guided in part by Skilling, who he was =
grooming as a successor.=20
