lion, and Enron's shareholders received a total return three times that of t=
he S&P 500. The company, which had revenues of $101 billion in 2000, markets=
 electricity and natural gas, delivers physical commodities, and provides fi=
nancial and risk-management services to customers around the world. It has a=
lso developed an intelligent network platform to facilitate online business.=
=20
In an exclusive interview on Aug. 20 with BusinessWeek Dallas Correspondent =
Stephanie Anderson Forest, Lay discussed Skilling's resignation, the search =
for a permanent successor, and the future of Enron. Here are edited excerpts=
 from their conversation:=20
Q: Since his official resignation announcement Aug. 14, Mr. Skilling has sin=
ce added that one of those personal reasons included Enron's falling stock p=
rice on his watch. A declining stock price doesn't seem like a very personal=
 reason.=20
