re seasoned than others. They are all very strong candidates who understand =
our business and our culture. In every case, [the candidates] have been here=
 several years, and, in some cases, 11 or 12 years. These are not unseasoned=
 people.=20
Q: So, whoever makes it to the office of the chairman has a shot at being En=
ron's next CEO?=20
A: Yes, but I have made it very clear that although they certainly will be o=
